Hi Janai and Jen,

Apologies for the late response, and thank you for your patience. We’ve looked into the credit card issue and have identified exactly what’s happening.

The Cause:
On 16 December, the “Gravity Forms Stripe” plugin on your website were updated to Version 6.0. This was a major security update that changed how the website communicates with Stripe.

Because of this, your site now requires a re-login to Stripe via the WordPress dashboard to authorise the new connection. Until this is done, the credit card field will remain hidden to protect your customers’ data.

The Fix (what you need to do):
Since we don’t have your Stripe login, please follow these 4 quick steps to refresh the connection in the https://syd-proposal.novaricollective.com.au website:
  1. Log in to your WordPress Dashboard.
  2. Go to Forms > Settings in the left menu, then click on the Stripe tab.
  3. You’ll see a “Connected to Stripe” message. Click the white “Disconnect From Stripe” button.
  4. Once the page refreshes, click the blue “Connect with Stripe” button and log in with your Stripe username and password.

This will instantly refresh the security keys and restore the credit card input field.

Please give it a go and let us know once it’s done, or if you run into any problems. If there's anything else we can help with, always happy to support!
